  • Type Parameters:
    KeyType - the type of the keys stored in the multimap
    ValueType - the type of the values stored in the multimap
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.google.common.collect.Multimap<KeyType,ValueType>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    EVMBasedQueryResultMultimap

    public abstract class QueryResultMultimap<KeyType,ValueType>
extends QueryResultAssociativeStore<KeyType,ValueType>
implements com.google.common.collect.Multimap<KeyType,ValueType>
    Implementation of Multimap interface to represent query results. A query result multimap takes a model query, with a specified key (input/source) parameter and a value (output/target) parameter.

    Apart from the standard multimap behavior, it is possible to register listeners that are notified when the contents of the multimap change.

    Subclasses of the query result multimap can attach to any query evaluation engine and shoug
